communications.communication:

Pursuant to the Ohio Open Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

All body-worn camera footage from Toledo Police officers responding on August 10, 2025 to a welfare check/animal complaint at a residence on Raymer Boulevard, Toledo, OH, where officers discovered 13 children living in unsafe and unsanitary conditions.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Daniel Wilkinson

communications.communication:

File 66-HQ-19073, captioned "Bureau Plans - Operation Alert 1960".

Please conduct a search of the Central Records System, including but not limited to the Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) Indices, the Microphone Surveillance (MISUR) Indices, the Physical Surveillance (FISUR) Indices, and the Technical Surveillance (TESUR) Indices, for both main-file records and cross-reference records for all relevant names, individuals, agencies and companies. The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

title: CIA Records on Information Asymmetry and Disinformation

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: CIA Records on Information Asymmetry and Disinformation
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

reports, memoranda, training materials, assessments, cables, after-action reviews, or studies created or held by the CIA from January 1, 1945 to the present that address, reference, or analyze:
A) Mechanisms of Information Asymmetry (How it is Used):
The intentional creation or exploitation of information asymmetry between elites/governments and the public (domestic or foreign).
The use of disinformation, misinformation, propaganda, psychological operations (psyops), influence operations, or perception management to cultivate confusion or controlled ignorance.
Case studies or after-action reports where partial truths or limited disclosure were used to stabilize regimes, neutralize opposition, or shape public opinion.
Analyses weighing intentional manipulation vs. unintended error in information operations or governance outcomes.
B) Underlying “20% Information” (The Content Itself):
5. Internal guides, handbooks, doctrine, or tradecraft materials that describe thresholds for effective information asymmetry (e.g., how much the public must or must not know for an operation to succeed).
6. Metrics, models, or evaluations that measure the level of public awareness/ignorance required for successful influence operations.
7. Collections of narrative templates, messaging frameworks, or “best practices” for framing, agenda-setting, normalization, distraction, or division designed to mask or camouflage manipulation.
Suggested program keywords to aid your search (non-exhaustive):
Office of Policy Coordination (OPC), OSS (Office of Strategic Services), psychological warfare, propaganda, influence operations, perception management, disinformation, active measures, Operation Mockingbird, “behavioral” or “cognitive” influence, audience segmentation, plausible deniability, limited hangout, media assets, error vs manipulation, information asymmetry.
If portions of these records are exempt, please release all reasonably segregable material. If my request is denied in whole or in part, please justify all deletions by reference to specific FOIA exemptions.
I am willing to pay reasonable duplication and search fees up to $50. If fees will exceed this amount, please contact me before proceeding. I also respectfully request a fee waiver, as disclosure of the requested materials would contribute significantly to public understanding of government activities.
Thank you for your assistance.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

Politicians on both sides of the aisle have also called attention to excessive use of sensitive data by this administration. For example, on April 9, 18 Senators wrote to the Treasury Inspector General for Tax Administration (TIGTA) investingdation access to ICE access of taxpayer information.**

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rebecca Williams

communications.subject: Florida Sunshine Law Request: FL mDL Program Records (Jan 2023–Present)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

Internal evaluation or pilot assessment reports that summarize performance, adoption, risks, or “lessons learned” from the mDL program, as well as documents that explain, evaluate, or justify why the program was paused, suspended, decommissioned, or otherwise put on hold (including budgetary, technical, policy, or accessibility issues), and any materials discussing the possibility of resuming or reactivating the program.

Agreements, contracts, or memoranda of understanding with vendors or partners, including but not limited to Thales, AAMVA, Apple, Google, Samsung, or other providers.

Interagency or interstate coordination documents, including but not limited to MOUs or correspondence with AAMVA or other states regarding mDL interoperability, standards development, or airport integration at Miami International Airport.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Rebecca Williams
